Text: My new book's deadline is tomorrow...

In a hotel room, Beta's other persona, Natsume Kafka,
is getting anxious.

Though the deadline is tomorrow, the page on the desk
in front of her is blank, with not one letter written.
It's down to the wire... Heheh.

It's actually getting interesting now that I'm up
against a wall... But this is no time for jokes!

I used to dream of being a writer, holed up in a
hotel until I finish my novel, and now here I am...

It was only fun for the first few days. Now, I've got
a blank manuscript and I'm under pressure from
my editor.
Ugh... My stomach's in knots.
Mind you...

Lady Alpha said I could take my time as we don't have
any urgent missions right now... I can do this!
I can do...this...
Natsume's voice fades and she lets out a deep sigh.

I tried to be positive, but I wish I could go on a
mission to escape from this reality...

If only Lady Alpha hadn't locked me up in here to
write. She's so mean.
Huh? Who are you calling mean?

Oh! I-I'm sorry! I don't really think you're mean,
Lady Alpha!
I-I must be so stressed that I'm hearing things.
*sigh*... I was given a week.

One week's enough time to finish it. Or so the editor
and I both thought. But in hindsight...
We were short-sighted...
The look on the editor's face the other day...

She was smiling when she said "You can do it,
Natsume!" but her eyes were cold. If I don't
finish this by tomorrow, she'll kill me...
Okay, stop being fatalistic! I must face reality!

With determination, Natsume returns to the task of
writing her manuscript.
Hmm...

Shall I call room service...for a coffee to keep me
awake?

Wait, there's some coffee left over from this
morning... Ugh! Cold coffee is disgusting...
Come on, concentrate!

Just psyching myself up doesn't help... Nothing is
coming to mind at all!

In the past, she listened to lots of folk stories.
As she writes down ideas, the slips of paper
on her desk grow and spread out.

I have an idea from the plentiful store of knowledge
bestowed on me by Master Shadow!

It's original enough to write a novel that might even
surprise my readers... I can—
Natsume's facial expression tightens.
—n't finish it!

This isn't original... I've written it before. Where
are all my new ideas?!

With everything being used in previous novels, she
can't think of anything fresh at all. This won't go
down well with her readers.

Hey, all of the author Natsume's recent novels are
too similar, don't you think? I want more variety!
I'm sure that's what they will say.

Oh, Master Shadow! I-I'll get him to tell me
a new story...

Master Shadow's well of wisdom never runs dry!
By tapping into his power, I can snap out of this
writer's block!

Just as soon as a sliver of light appears it vanishes,
and she shakes her head weakly.

Hmm, no. I shouldn't bother Master Shadow with my
personal problems when he's busy. I must rely on
my own abilities!
There must be something I can do...

Natsume had writer's block in the past too. She has
rarely found writing novels easy.

Still, these pains of labor go hand in hand with the
pleasure of writing fiction.

But this time is completely different, as she does not
have a clue where to begin or what to write.
I might not get through this...

But...my fans are expecting a new novel from me. If I
can't snap out of this, they'll be so disappointed.

In Natsume's mind, a crowd of fans' faces lining up
for an autograph appear one after the other.

Natsume! I'll be sure to buy your new novel on book-
launch day!
Please read the letter I've written you!
I'm your biggest fan! Can I have your autograph?

When I made my debut, I could count the number of
fans at my autograph session on one hand...

I remember the faces of those people who came as if
it was yesterday.

The little girl who saved up bit by bit to buy my
book. The mother and daughter who told me they
were fans.

The father who accompanied his daughter to my signing
session and then became a fan himself.
Oh yeah. Even Princess Rose lined up for my autograph.

Natsume recalls Rose blushing as she held out the
book. In that instant, she wasn't a princess, but just
a girl who loved her book.

The fans... At first I wrote for the joy of writing,
but the fans' energy was powerful.

Having them constantly in my thoughts helped to
inspire me...
The thought of my fans energizes me... Heehee.

A common storyline is when the protaganist, defeated
once by his nemesis, rises for a second time, cheered
on by loved ones...

But its popularity makes it a simple plot to develop,
which is why it's so common...
A simple...plot to develop?

Master Shadow told me many folk tales with those
simple storylines, and I loved them.

Yet, I thought I had to write something new, original
or sophisticated... That's all I could think about.

A simple, noble story works great. So that's what
I'll write about. The kind of story I love.

I wonder if my fans will be happy... Will they say
I'm too one-dimensional?
Natsume raises her head uneasily. However...

I trust in myself to do this justice, and in my fans
who've loved my novels for so long.

She raises her face, lit by the light from a gap in
the curtain, and then plants it on the desk as if to
sleep.

M-Mmm... Phew, it must be morning...hm?
It's almost afternoon?!
Oh no, the manuscript...!

I think I recall finishing it... But what if that just
happened in my dream...?

A hurried search finds the manuscript covered in her
handwriting on the desk.
Thank goodness... It wasn't a dream.
Worries over, a wave of relaxation washes over her.

I did it...I finished my novel. Oh, I'm so tired,
but...I feel a sense of achievement. I hope that
my fans enjoy it.

As Natsume rises unsteadily, she suddenly flops
backwards onto the bed.

Anyway...let me lie here on the bed until my editor
comes for the manuscript...

Natsume falls once again into a deep sleep, with a
contented smile on her lips.
